Description: Ostracon, fragment of the upper-body of a red-brown pottery vessel, the interior is lightly covered with a dark-brown resinous deposit, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and remains of one line of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393773) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393773)
